summary: This is a travel authorization notification for a DOJ trip related to the Epstein investigation, specifically for a witness interview in Beverly Hills, CA from February 26-29, 2020. The document shows ongoing investigative activity by the Department of Justice in early 2020.

events.title: Planned Witness Interview for Epstein Investigation
events.description: A witness interview related to the Epstein investigation was scheduled to take place in Beverly Hills, CA.

keyFacts: The Department of Justice was conducting witness interviews for the Epstein investigation as of February 2020.
A specific travel authorization (11061344-1) was approved for travel to Beverly Hills, CA from February 26-29, 2020.
The purpose was listed as 'R20NYS13402 - Epstein Investigation - Witness interview'.
The document shows ongoing investigative activity nearly six months after Epstein's death in August 2019.
The travel authorization system used was E2 Solutions within the DOJ network.
